CommisarRoberts,"2020-03-28T11:15:48.963Z","A decent edition to the Microfighters series","

Bought this set on a whim from a local supermarket for about 9 pounds. Its a nice little set which when built looks very nice next to the other micro fighter ships.

column2: t too many parts to this set and it takes about 5-10 minutes to build with the build being rather enjoyable. The ship has two stud guns attached to it which fire out like lasers which add a certain level of playability to the set.

column1: The Kylo Ren minifigure which comes with the set is very well designed and will be a great addition to a minifigure collection.
All in all this is a nice set, while it certainly is not a challenging one to make I think it makes a fine addition to any Lego Star Wars collection well worth a purchase!

column3: s Shuttle Microfighter which released in 2020. This set also was released in the first wave of 2020 Star Wars sets. It retails for $9.99, has 72 pieces, one minifigure, and is from episode 9 The Rise of Skywalker. This is available at retail stores.

column1: The Kylo Ren minifigure we get is the same minifigure we get from all the other sets accept for episode 7 lego sets. He comes with no cape and the details on his helmet is just AMAZING! This helmet is from episode 7, now use with red glue to keep it together. Kylo Ren has a &ldquo
column3: face while on the other side it has an angry face. He also comes with his lightsaber.

column16: The small sized shuttle has to adjustable wings with 1 green stud shooter on each side, red lights in the front to single where the cockpit is, and two engines on the back. The minifigure fits perfectly inside the Microfighter and overall is just a great addition to your Microfighter collection.

Opening
This one of the best micro fighters an the one with the best character and the build is of a very nice ship in universe .
The figure has a very nice helmet mould with menacing red cracks accurate to the film that I don'
column2: t really like , the head is dual sided and has a face which is very emotionless and an incredibly enraged face accurate to the character , the torso is nice with the chain mail looking print continuing onto the legs and his accessory is his crossbows lightsaber which is a nice piece but amazingly inaccurate .

column1: The build has two identical wing builds which slope up to a point and have the single sticking out forward point in each , the wings a fairly detailed with tiles and a stud shooter for each , the cockpit has a sloped construction around the window , a printed control panel , greebleing detail at the rear and two thrusters and the wings when attached have a very wide range of motion .
this is a very good micro fighter with
column2: no flaws other than the obviously inaccurate lightsaber hilt and blade although it would it would have been nice to get a cape and hair piece but they are not too rare , so overall I recommend it to anyone who either doesn&#39
